Nigeria Raises Bonny Light, Qua Premium for April to $3.40

-- B y   S h e r r y   S u
-- 
2011-03-22T12:47:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/nigeria-raises-bonny-light-qua-premium-for-april-to-3-40-1-.html
Nigeria raised the official selling
price of its benchmark Qua Iboe and Bonny Light crude oil
exports in April by $1.25 a barrel, according to a price list
obtained by Bloomberg News.  Exports of the two grades will be priced at $3.40 a barrel
above the North Sea Dated Brent benchmark next month, according
to the price list released by stated owned Nigerian National
Petroleum Corp.  The official selling price of  Equatorial Guinea â€™s Zafiro,
also set by NNPC, was raised to 40 cents above Dated Brent from
10 cents.  The following table shows details of official selling
prices of Nigeria crudes against Dated Brent. Prices are in
